<!--
  P-A / BUILD-1 — Seed missing operating-expense accounts.

  "Odoo accounting as-is": the 47 accounts of Odoo's generic chart are
  load-bearing (the invoice engine posts to them) and are NOT touched here.
  This file ADDS only the operating-expense accounts that chart lacks for a
  Zimbabwe event-production business — a sensible STARTER set, NOT a copy of
  Zoho's 33 (drifted) categories, which stay in the read-only neon_migration
  archive.

  REUSED (existing — deliberately NOT recreated, no duplicate):
    611000 Purchase of Equipments · 612000 Rent · 620000 Bank Fees
    630000 Salary Expenses
  NON-EXPENSE items map to existing accounts (created here: none):
    Fixed assets (Computer Equipment / Plant & Machinery / Furniture)
        -> 151000 Fixed Asset (asset_fixed)
    VAT -> 131000 Tax Paid (input) / 251000 Tax Received (output)
           (+ 132000 Tax Receivable / 252000 Tax Payable)
    Employee advance (staff receivable, current asset)
        -> NO dedicated account exists today; surfaced for Robin's review,
           NOT built in this expense-only round.

  CODES: gap-filled in the 6xxxxx expense band, avoiding the occupied
  600000/611000/612000/620000/630000/641000/642000/643000. Grouped by theme
  (premises -> motor/travel -> office -> people -> professional/marketing).

  ⚠️ DECISION (noupdate="1"): chart-of-accounts seed is config-as-data the
  bookkeeper then owns. noupdate keeps later UI edits (rename/reparent/
  archive) from being clobbered by a future -u. Records load once on first
  install of this data file; codes are unique so re-running -u is a no-op.
-->
<odoo noupdate="1">

    <!-- ═══ Premises & utilities ═══ -->
    <record id="account_op_electricity_utilities" model="account.account">
        <field name="code">613000</field>
        <field name="name">Electricity &amp; Utilities</field>
        <field name="account_type">expense</field>
        <field name="company_id" ref="base.main_company"/>
        <field name="neon_source">seed_accounting</field>
    </record>

